00:19:39.340 --> 00:19:42.360
Parents ask me, you know,
"What advice do you have?

00:19:42.360 --> 00:19:43.970
What advice do you
have for my kids

00:19:43.970 --> 00:19:45.270
to keep them interested in math?

00:19:45.270 --> 00:19:46.570
To just help them in
general, besides the,

00:19:46.570 --> 00:19:47.870
you know, the instruction?"

00:19:47.870 --> 00:19:49.170
And there are a couple
things that I say to parents.

00:19:49.170 --> 00:19:50.470
One is, from the earliest
time you possibly can,

00:19:50.470 --> 00:19:51.770
point out math, in
the real world.

00:19:51.770 --> 00:19:53.070
Just demonstrate.

00:19:53.070 --> 00:19:54.370
It can shopping at the grocery
store, and you're showing,

00:19:54.370 --> 00:19:55.670
you know, if you buy three
pounds of turkey and it costs,

00:19:55.670 --> 00:19:56.970
you know, $5 a pound, you know,

00:19:56.970 --> 00:19:58.270
show the multiplication
in the real world.

00:19:58.270 --> 00:19:59.570
Show it around them.

00:19:59.570 --> 00:20:00.870
Or show them the same thing
in reverse, with division.

00:20:00.870 --> 00:20:02.170
If we've got this much money and
it costs this much, per pound,

00:20:02.170 --> 00:20:03.470
how many pounds can we buy?

00:20:03.470 --> 00:20:04.770
Just show them how it's actually
all around us all the time,

00:20:04.770 --> 00:20:06.070
because it is amazing to
me how many people say,

00:20:06.070 --> 00:20:08.750
"When am I ever going to
use math in real life?"

00:20:08.750 --> 00:20:10.050
What about money?

00:20:10.050 --> 00:20:12.880
Money makes the world go round.

00:20:12.880 --> 00:20:16.020
